# Song Mode State

- `SongModeProvider` owns the local snapshot and serialized persistence queue. Route all snapshot mutations through `commitSnapshot` (or helpers built on it); do not mix ad-hoc `setSnapshot(...)` calls with direct IndexedDB writes.
- Keep persistence optimistic in React state, then serialize database writes behind the queue. If a change adds substantial CRUD logic, extract hooks/helpers instead of growing the provider with another large inline mutator.
- The app shell owns header action slots in `src/components/song-mode/app-chrome.tsx`. Route-level controls should render into those contexts with `createPortal` instead of duplicating header chrome inside feature views.
- TanStack routes live in `src/routes/` and are registered by file-based routing. Add routes with `createFileRoute`; never hand-edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts`.
- IndexedDB schema changes belong in `src/lib/song-mode/db.ts` `openDB(..., { upgrade })` migrations with a version bump. Keep `song-mode-provider-hydration.ts` for temporary compatibility cleanup, not permanent schema migration logic.
